# Stale Next.js export artifacts.
#
# Next.js's `output: "export"` mode produces different file layouts depending
# on `trailingSlash`:
#   - trailingSlash: false (current) -> route.html       (e.g. api-reference.html)
#   - trailingSlash: true            -> route/index.html (e.g. api-reference/index.html)
#
# When a build with one setting runs over a working tree that has artifacts
# from the other setting, the stale files linger as untracked. They've shown
# up in commits before (1ba2be77 added them, de790fd2 removed them) and keep
# resurfacing whenever a developer's local environment produces the other
# format. Only the top-level index.html is canonical for our config; ignore
# any nested index.html so it stops cluttering `git status`.
index.html
!/index.html
